Morgan Le Fay <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usabatiniscratch.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sabatini Scratch</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/27/01 8:51:54 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.blackarcana.com/camelot/scratchcam1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Melee</span><hr size=1> Leading off with your biggest crit move in the first round of combat (i.e. perf artery, etc) gives you the same life expectancy as a wizard who nukes in that same time period. Of course you're going to die because your main tank had no chance to gain aggro, especially if you keep doing normal dual swings after.<br>
<br>
I've been in more than one group that the infiltrator was lectured like a small child because he did that. It's sad to say that assassin types are liked better in groups that they don't use their best moves on. Healers hate being stuck in groups with manasinks. <br>
<br>
I think it's why I started feeling like a 5th wheel at times playing mine. Melee types can't get away with hanging back until a target is aggroed enough like a wizard would.  Not to mention that even attempting do do so in a standard multiple pull situation is a waste of time.<br>
<br>
Poison isn't terribly useful either on the average pull. Things tend to die quickly enough that it's a waste of time and money. It's best saved for debuffing during special situations.<br>
<br>
So really what makes you best in RvR makes you a liability in PvE. Your best bet is to stick to normal moves and hope your group doesn't notice you aren't pulling your weight as much as the other 7 in your group. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :\ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":\"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udisdain1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Disdain1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/27/01 9:17:05 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Melee</span><hr size=1> &quot;and hope your group doesn't notice you aren't pulling your weight as much as the other 7 in your group.&quot;<br>
<br>
Assassins just aren't very useful in the standard full grp killing purples.  They are much more useful in a small grp 2-3 pulling oranges and reds.<br>
<br>
As an inf, my best partner is an equal level pally:<br>
- best taunter in Albion.  Only class which can hold aggro off me more than 95% of time.<br>
- can protect me<br>
- can guard me<br>
- tanks very well<br>
- heal chant heals the 1-2 hits I take before he pulls aggro<br>
<br>
Pally likes having an inf as partner (or at least to him it doesnt make alot of difference whether its an inf/armsman/merc)<br>
- we can pull (a skill they lack)<br>
- open with enervating drops a fair amount of hp<br>
- melee + DOT poison (refresh as needed) does ok damage on oranges and low reds since poison usually sticks (purples almost always resist)<br>
<br>
This combo has almost no down time.   Since I usually end the battle at almost full health, I try not to use more than 50% stamina (pincer is great to conserve stamina).  So I'm off pulling as he regains the rest of his stamina and the mob arrives just as he is fully recovered.<br>
<br>
Add a cleric to this grp and take reds down easily.<br>
<br>
I'm not saying we have more to offer this grp compared to an armsman/merc etc.  But we can carry our weight in small grps with a good tank. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showMessage?topicID=1428.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showMessage?topicID=1475.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.emailToFriend?topicID=1474.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.threadControl?topicID=1474.topic><img src=http://www.evercrack.net/shpics/closeThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1474.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1474.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub35.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion">Main Lounge<option value="thesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc">News Bulletin<option value="thesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies">Training Studio<option value="thesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers">The Back Alley<option value="thesafehousefrm13">Quests of Norrath<option value="thesafehousetherootcellar">The Root Cellar<option 